tum optimization, even if\naffected by random noise, is still potentially faster than any classical\nalgorithm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Jul 2014 20:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Nov 2014 21:00:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 15 Dec 2015 19:02:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-16"}
